{{See|adam}}
==English==
===Etymology===
From Hebrew [[אדם|אָדָם]] (adam) "earth", "man", "soil", "light brown" < [[אדמה]] (adamah) 'red earth', 'ground'.

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Adam'''

# The first man in the [[Bible]] and the [[Koran]], the [[progenitor]] of the [[human race]].<!--encyclopedic info; does not refine the definition: With his wife [[Eve]] he fathered two sons, [[Cain]] and [[Abel]].-->
# A male [[given name]].
# (''figuratively'') [[original sin|Original sin]]; human frailty.

